		{
			dependencies: ["4B46EF307977674F"]
			description: [
				"&o&7The AE2 in-game guide has a MUCH better explanation of Spatial Storage than this questline, so if you need more help, try looking there.&r"
				""
				"&6Spatial Storage&r is a mechanic in AE2 that allows you to &bcut-and-paste a selected area&r, wherever you desire."
				""
				"To get started, craft some &6Spatial Pylons&r, used to select the area to work with."
				""
				"Note that a valid Pylon &cmust be placed in a straight line&r, and cannot have bends."
				""
				"Each line of Pylons will consume its own channel."
			]
			id: "5C58E168DB13B1AA"
			min_width: 250
			rewards: [{
				id: "403B08915BAD14A3"
				type: "xp"
				xp: 20
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "0A41B737ECA02110"
				item: "ae2:spatial_pylon"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Spatial Storage"
			x: 1.0d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["5C58E168DB13B1AA"]
			description: [
				"The &6Spatial IO Port&r is responsible for performing actions regarding &bmoving things in and out&r of Spatial Storage."
				""
				"Note that the &b\"Efficiency\"&r value is represented by how many &bSpatial Pylons&r are in the selected area. &6The higher the Efficiency, the lower the power cost.&r"
				""
				"To use, insert a &bSpatial Storage Cell&r into the left slot, then provide the IO Port with a &bredstone pulse&r &7(such as a Button)&r to swap the contents of the Spatial Cell with the contents of the selected area."
				""
				"Note that performing swap actions with the IO Port will take &can extreme amount of power&r, but it is not constant."
			]
			id: "125316F0D3A537A3"
			min_width: 250
			rewards: [{
				id: "495D16D5E7B98CCD"
				type: "xp"
				xp: 20
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "1F637BC823FAAA0E"
				item: "ae2:spatial_io_port"
				type: "item"
			}]
			x: 0.5d
			y: -2.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["5C58E168DB13B1AA"]
			description: [
				"&6Spatial Storage Cells&r will store the data needed to access an area within Spatial Storage. These are used with the &6IO Port&r to act as a &b\"clipboard\" of sorts&r in the cut-and-paste paradigm."
				""
				"Note that once a Spatial Storage Cell has been written to with a specific size of area, it &cCANNOT be rewritten with a different size&r. You must &bmake a new Cell&r to use a differently sized area."
				""
				"This is important as these Cells cannot rotate wither. &cA 4x4x8 area is NOT the same as an 8x4x4 area&r according to these Cells."
			]
			id: "510F9849ACDF6132"
			rewards: [{
				id: "5E5A6502A67B02F3"
				type: "xp"
				xp: 20
			}]
			tasks: [{
