		{
			dependencies: [
				"125316F0D3A537A3"
				"510F9849ACDF6132"
			]
			description: [
				"Use the &6AE2 in-game guide&r to set up a Spatial Storage setup &7(build an SCS)&r. Then, &binsert your Spatial Storage Cell into the IO Port&r and &bprovide a redstone pulse&r. You'll notice that &6anything&r in the defined area &7(the SCS)&r will have disappeared,&6 including entities&r."
				""
				"Putting the same Storage Cell back into the IO Port and providing another redstone pulse will &bbring back the contents&r stored in Spatial Storage. If you had placed more things in the defined area while something was already stored, you'll notice that the &bcontents have instead been swapped&r."
				""
				"Note that Spatial Storage stores everything in a &6separate dimension&r, which is important to note if you intend on putting anything functional inside."
			]
			id: "4ACFC616E3663F90"
